-- GMA Network, Metro Pacific, San Miguel: Philippine Stock Preview
-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 2012-03-02T00:42:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/gma-network-metro-pacific-san-miguel-philippine-stock-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  Philippine (PASHR)   trading . Stock symbols are
in parentheses and share prices are as of yesterday’s close.  The  Philippine Stock Exchange Index (PCOMP)  rose 0.8 percent to
4,938.61.  GMA Network Inc. (GMA7)  (GMA7 PM): Philippine Long Distance
Telephone Co. Chairman Manuel Pangilinan said his group is
“interested to take a look” at the broadcasting company. It
isn’t in talks to acquire GMA, he said. The stock increased 0.8
percent to 9.68 pesos.  Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  : The company with
investments in water, power and health care said profit rose 76
percent to 5.06 billion pesos last year. Consolidated revenue
increased 19 percent to 22.07 billion pesos, the company said in
a statement. It declared a dividend of 1.50 centavos a share.
The stock gained 0.9 percent to 3.54 pesos.  San Miguel Corp. (SMC)  : The company said it’s finalizing
the acquisition of Exxon Mobil Corp.’s refining business in
Malaysia through its Petron Corp. unit.  San Miguel is also in talks to sell its controlling stake
in Bank of Commerce to Malaysia’s  CIMB Group Holdings Bhd. (CIMB) , it
said in a disclosure to the stock exchange yesterday. The stock
rose 1.8 percent to 115 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cecilia Yap in Manila at 
